    public static class Semantics.WritingState
extends Semantics.MappingState
    This class implements the possible state for a semantic writing process.

    In particular, this class extend Semantics.MappingState by adding to more states: ADDED and UPDATED.

    Thus, possible states for a Semantics.writeSemantics() and Array3D.SemanticMap.writeSemantics( Semantics.Descriptor) processes are:

    • Semantics.MappingState.ERROR: implemented in Semantics.MappingState,
    • Semantics.MappingState.INCONSISTENT: implemented in Semantics.MappingState,
    • Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED: implemented in Semantics.MappingState,
    • ADD: the writing operation produced something new in the semantic description,
    • UPDATE: the writing operation changed the semantic of something.

    REMARK: extending classes must have static state fields assigned to inter values bigger than UPDATED.

      • combineResults

        public static Semantics.WritingState combineResults(Semantics.WritingState r1,
                                                    Semantics.WritingState r2)
        Merges two writings states and generates an output feasible state.

        In particular, it returns:

        • Semantics.MappingState.INCONSISTENT: if at lest one state is in inconsistent state,
        • Semantics.MappingState.ERROR: if at least one state is in error state,
        • Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED: if both did not change nothing. If only one input parameter is in Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED state, it returns the other.
        • UPDATED: if both update something in the semantics. If only one input parameter is in UPDATED state, it returns the other.
        • ADDED: if is not one of the case above.

        Parameters:
        r1 - the first writing state to merge.
        r2 - the second writing state to merge.
        Returns:
        a new writing state obtained from the combination of the input parameters.
